1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:02,710
But I've...

2
00:00:03,870 --> 00:00:05,040
already made up my mind.

3
00:00:08,430 --> 00:00:09,430
Huh?

4
00:00:11,740 --> 00:00:13,160
I'm not going to run away anymore.

5
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:22,850
Are you...

6
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:27,560
still mad?

7
00:00:34,210 --> 00:00:35,210
No...

8
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,990
I've just been thinking

9
00:00:41,620 --> 00:00:46,650
about everything you've said and done.

10
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,520
Wait... what?

11
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:55,270
So, basically...

12
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:56,620
it's like this.

13
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:59,240
Because of your trauma from being bullied,

14
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,510
you were scared to fall for me,

15
00:01:02,540 --> 00:01:06,540
so you went to Kanda-san for comfort.

16
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:09,240
And then?

17
00:01:09,650 --> 00:01:13,090
You hated yourself for
being weak and manipulative,

18
00:01:14,630 --> 00:01:18,970
and thought you weren't
good enough for me... right?

19
00:01:23,830 --> 00:01:30,080
I guess... I've always had low self-esteem.

20
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:37,840
And after things went south with that guy,

21
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:42,220
I lost what little confidence I had left.

22
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:46,590
Looking back, it was
the same with my brother.

23
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:51,520
I didn't actually feel
that inferior to him,

24
00:01:55,010 --> 00:01:56,980
but I forced myself to think I did.

25
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,360
I didn't want to hope
for anything in the future,

26
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:10,550
just so I wouldn't get
hurt like that again.

27
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,160
The "Akira" I see

28
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:24,690
is just a version of you that's in my head.

29
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,200
Even if it's just on the surface,

30
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:33,270
I feel like that's a part of who I am.

31
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,630
But...

32
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,540
I'm starting to lose
track of who I really am.

33
00:02:55,910 --> 00:02:56,910
In that case,

34
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,030
how about I'm the one who uncovers it?

35
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:10,350
Everything about you.

36
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:12,730
Wait, what?!

37
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:19,210
Stop it. What are you imagining?

38
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:20,900
You've got a dirty mind, Akira.

39
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,770
I do not! I wasn't thinking about that.

40
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:24,480
What do you mean by "that"?

41
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,030
I told you, it's... never mind.

42
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:31,650
It's okay.

43
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:35,260
You're fine just the way you are.

44
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:40,160
Don't force yourself to change.

45
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:42,950
It's okay if you don't
know who you are yet.

46
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,870
Because to me,

47
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:49,630
you've always been perfectly clear.

48
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:01,070
Just stay in my shadow forever.

49
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:11,550
Kanata...

50
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:16,950
Your name has the
character for "sun" in it, right?

51
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,600
So you're the one who's
supposed to light up my life.

52
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,480
Hey, why are you crying?

53
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:37,230
I guess I'm lucky to see a
side of you no one else does.

54
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:45,460
Idiot...

55
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,060
Alright.

56
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:51,460
I guess that means we've made up.

57
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,160
Yeah...

58
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:01,630
Come on.

59
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,720
How long are you going to cry for?

60
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:05,650
Your face is a total mess.

61
00:05:07,570 --> 00:05:08,570
Here.

62
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,500
"Contrast"

63
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,600
(Episode 8: To Stop Wandering)

64
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:08,610
Man, this really is
the best place to relax.

65
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,950
The construction finished
sooner than I thought.

66
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:16,290
Oh.

67
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,599
By the way, practice was canceled today.

68
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,950
Are you busy after school?

69
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:21,740
Sorry.

70
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:23,250
I have a career counseling session.

71
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:28,370
Wait a second.

72
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,840
Isn't your class doing
those today too, Kanata?

73
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:33,150
Is that so?

74
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,120
Oh, right.

75
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,500
I think I remember something about that.

76
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,880
You really need to keep
track of these things.

77
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,270
So, Akira.

78
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:47,589
You said you wanted to go to college.

79
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:49,030
Do you have a specific goal in mind?

80
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:50,830
Well...

81
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:52,890
I have a few top choices.

82
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:56,990
I'm looking at schools
with strong law programs.

83
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,070
It'll give me more career options later on.

84
00:07:02,850 --> 00:07:03,850
I see...

85
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:18,660
But with your current
grades, those schools...

86
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:22,360
A recommendation will be tough.

87
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:24,780
I know...

88
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:37,760
If you're still serious about soccer,

89
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:41,530
why not try out for the
selection match next year?

90
00:07:42,050 --> 00:07:43,500
The selection match?

91
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:44,780
With my skill level...

92
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,830
The odds are definitely against you.

93
00:07:47,950 --> 00:07:50,190
And you'll be up against
the best players in the region.

94
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,630
But it's still worth a
shot, don't you think?

95
00:07:56,500 --> 00:08:02,800
(2027 Season Selection Match Confirmed)

96
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,380
Thank you, Coach.

97
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:45,720
I like you.

98
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,030
I already know what your answer is.

99
00:08:52,890 --> 00:08:53,890
But I...

100
00:08:54,260 --> 00:08:56,020
I just really wanted
you to know how I feel.

101
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:58,190
Yeah.

102
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,200
Thank you.

103
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,590
I don't have those feelings for you,

104
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:04,410
but I appreciate you letting me know.

105
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,230
Man, this is bad.

106
00:09:33,730 --> 00:09:35,960
- These are filthy.
- They really are.

107
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:38,150
I wonder if this will even come out.

108
00:09:45,490 --> 00:09:48,699
Washing shoes with you like this

109
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:50,400
takes me back to elementary school.

110
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,220
Yeah.

111
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:53,670
I guess it does.

112
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,320
Hey, Kanata.

113
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:04,120
Have you decided what
you're doing after graduation?

114
00:10:07,566 --> 00:10:09,126
I haven't really given it much thought.

115
00:10:10,970 --> 00:10:11,970
Oh, okay.

116
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:13,450
What's up?

117
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:19,260
I was thinking...

118
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,920
about studying abroad.

119
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,270
Wait, seriously?

120
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,700
Yeah.

121
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:31,290
I haven't told Mom yet, though.

122
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,200
I see.

123
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:38,910
The coach asked me if I wanted to

124
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,270
try going pro.

125
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:46,120
I'm not sure yet, though.

126
00:10:47,090 --> 00:10:48,810
You're going to keep playing soccer, right?

127
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,560
Who knows.

128
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,920
By the way, Kanata.

129
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:10,560
Did someone confess to you again?

130
00:12:12,610 --> 00:12:13,610
Huh?

131
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:15,530
Who told you that?

132
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:20,070
Was it those guys again?

133
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:22,020
No.

134
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,330
I just happened to overhear you guys

135
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,560
talking behind the gym.

136
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:28,210
Are you serious?

137
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:34,070
Man, you're something else.

138
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:37,050
Are you the most popular
guy in school or what?

139
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:39,810
Well... she's confessed to me before.

140
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,990
I just had to turn her down again.

141
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:51,040
She must really like you.

142
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:54,090
I mean, I appreciate it and all.

143
00:12:56,970 --> 00:12:59,540
I've never been popular,
so I wouldn't know,

144
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:02,830
but rejecting people
seems like a lot of work.

145
00:13:04,130 --> 00:13:05,130
That's why

146
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:08,320
the best I can do is say,
"I appreciate you letting me know.

147
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,250
I see...

148
00:13:18,370 --> 00:13:20,710
Man, it's freezing out here.

149
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:23,050
Can I huddle up with you?

150
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:25,040
Is that okay? Awesome.

151
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:27,549
What are you doing?

152
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:28,620
So warm.

153
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:47,270
Hmm?

154
00:13:49,070 --> 00:13:53,160
So, Akira... are you and Kanata dating?

155
00:13:59,820 --> 00:14:00,820
Wait, what?!

156
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:03,610
You were totally just
thinking of an excuse.

157
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:06,450
No, I wasn't...

158
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:09,490
Actually,

159
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,740
I've had a feeling for a while now.

160
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:14,970
Now I'm pretty much certain.

161
00:14:16,570 --> 00:14:19,170
You guys were fighting around
the time of the soccer match, right?

162
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:24,660
But ever since you made up,

163
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:28,730
Kanata spends every lunch break with you.

164
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:32,450
He used to never bring you up,

165
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:36,220
but lately, he can't
stop talking about you.

166
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:41,650
What exactly is he saying...?

167
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:44,880
So?

168
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:45,900
What's the deal?

169
00:14:51,630 --> 00:14:52,900
We're not...

170
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,270
dating...

171
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:58,610
What? Seriously?

172
00:14:59,090 --> 00:14:59,740
Yeah...

173
00:14:59,741 --> 00:15:01,720
Oh... but wait,

174
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:04,340
you like him too, don't you, Akira?

175
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:06,510
Well...

176
00:15:06,890 --> 00:15:07,670
Yeah...

177
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,030
Then it's totally mutual.

178
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,200
One hundred percent.

179
00:15:11,910 --> 00:15:13,429
Honestly, when Kanata talks about you,

180
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:14,550
he's basically just gushing.

181
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,080
Why don't you guys just date already?

182
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:22,830
But...

183
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:26,520
I have to study for exams and everything.

184
00:15:27,170 --> 00:15:28,570
And Kanata has his club activities.

185
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:31,140
Hmm...

186
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,490
Isn't that for you guys to decide?

187
00:15:42,890 --> 00:15:44,770
By the way, Mizuki...

188
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:47,340
Um...

189
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:50,790
Are you really okay with this?

190
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:52,670
With what?

191
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:56,650
Me and Kanata...

192
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:00,500
both being guys...

193
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:04,460
I don't see why that matters.

194
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:06,970
If anything,

195
00:16:06,971 --> 00:16:09,290
I'm more annoyed that
you aren't together yet.

196
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:12,960
But then again,

197
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:14,920
even if you aren't "dating,"

198
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,549
as long as you're on the same page,

199
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,000
that's not so bad either.

200
00:16:19,650 --> 00:16:21,340
You both know how the other feels, right?

201
00:16:23,610 --> 00:16:24,610
Well...

202
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:25,860
Yeah...

203
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,520
But

204
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,550
we haven't actually said it out loud.

205
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,720
Huh? What are you waiting for?

206
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:33,260
Just say it already.

207
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:35,869
Kanata would be so happy.

208
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:36,870
No...

209
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:41,280
I feel like I've dropped
plenty of hints already.

210
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,800
Well... then that's Kanata's problem.

211
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:49,780
Oh, but I'm not unhappy
with how things are.

212
00:16:50,690 --> 00:16:53,790
Really, I'm fine with the way we are now.

213
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:01,770
But wanting more than what you have...

214
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,400
isn't that what love is?

215
00:17:12,210 --> 00:17:13,410
Is it?

216
00:17:13,830 --> 00:17:14,830
Yeah.

217
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:36,019
Did you hear the rumor?

218
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:37,780
- Wait, what happened?
- You haven't heard?

219
00:17:37,810 --> 00:17:40,520
- They say Aoyama Senpai is leaving.
- No way, seriously?

220
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:44,020
I heard he got scouted and is dropping out.

221
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:47,200
- Then what's the point of even coming?
- Right?

222
00:17:47,540 --> 00:17:50,000
- Aoyama Senpai is so cool.
- I know, he's amazing.

223
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:59,179
- Ooh, I want some.
- Sure.

224
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,180
Yay!

225
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:02,290
Geez, what's going on?

226
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,140
Do you guys know where Kanata is?

227
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:07,120
- It's a confession marathon.
- Wait... what?

228
00:18:07,810 --> 00:18:11,050
The rumor about him
dropping out is everywhere.

229
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:13,329
Now there's a non-stop
line of girls confessing.

230
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:14,330
Jun!

231
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:16,850
Um... do you know where he went?

232
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,450
Oh, I think he left early today.

233
00:18:21,410 --> 00:18:23,900
He just left, so he should still be nearby.

234
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,270
Thank you!

235
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:31,990
Akira!

236
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:34,820
I'm going!

237
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:40,710
Go get him!

238
00:18:57,890 --> 00:18:58,890
What's the assembly for?

239
00:18:58,891 --> 00:19:00,050
No idea.

240
00:19:00,260 --> 00:19:01,540
Club? You mean in middle school?

241
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:04,269
Why'd you just stop like that?

242
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:05,800
Sorry, sorry, I dropped my phone.

243
00:19:11,570 --> 00:19:12,570
My bad.

244
00:19:12,870 --> 00:19:14,739
- Oh, okay.
- What instrument did you play?

245
00:19:14,740 --> 00:19:16,289
- Trumpet.
- Trumpet?!

246
00:19:16,290 --> 00:19:17,150
Pretty cool, right?

247
00:19:17,151 --> 00:19:18,480
- Not really.
- It's alright, I guess.

248
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:21,570
- It's okay.
- Hey, I was the section leader!

249
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,200
Kanata!

250
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,770
- Is that a BBQ bento?
- Yeah.

251
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:30,080
- Let me have a bite! Please?
- No way.

252
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:10,890
- That Salisbury steak is huge!
- Crazy, right?

253
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:11,990
You got a haircut.

254
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:13,900
It was starting to get annoying.

255
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,570
I didn't go too short, though.

256
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:17,550
Nice. I should probably get mine cut too.

257
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,150
Even if I get hurt,

258
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:25,080
or if I end up hurting someone else,

259
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,800
even so...

260
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,810
I still feel this way about you.

261
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:34,350
Kanata!

262
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:38,740
Akira?

263
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,420
I...

264
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,650
I don't want you to accept
anyone else's feelings anymore.

265
00:20:46,230 --> 00:20:47,940
I want mine to be the only ones you take.

266
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,350
I...

267
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:53,250
I love you.

268
00:20:55,190 --> 00:20:56,190
So... will you...

269
00:20:56,220 --> 00:20:57,220
Akira.

270
00:21:00,910 --> 00:21:01,910
I love you so much.

271
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:04,410
Be my boyfriend.

272
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:07,350
Wait...

273
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:10,950
Sorry for cutting you off.

274
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:13,850
But I'm so crazy about
you, I couldn't wait.

275
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:20,180
I won't accept anyone's feelings but yours.

276
00:21:25,460 --> 00:21:26,880
I heard you were dropping out.

277
00:21:28,790 --> 00:21:29,790
Oh...

278
00:21:30,420 --> 00:21:31,520
That was just a rumor.

279
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:35,790
I was just going to an info session.

280
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:39,780
You see,

281
00:21:43,290 --> 00:21:44,850
I want to become an athletic trainer.

282
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:48,470
So I was just looking
at vocational schools.

283
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:50,400
I have no idea how it turned into that.

284
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,520
Rumors are scary, huh?

285
00:21:57,210 --> 00:21:58,210
But why...?

286
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:02,850
I wanted to surprise you.

287
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,040
Just kidding.

288
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:10,290
Actually,

289
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:13,370
I was just trying to act cool.

290
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:17,500
I didn't want to keep
relying on you for everything.

291
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:19,780
I wanted to make a decision on my own.

292
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:25,420
I see.

293
00:22:28,820 --> 00:22:30,440
Will you support me?

294
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:34,730
Of course I will.

295
00:22:37,260 --> 00:22:38,460
Really?

296
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,980
Since you called me your "sun,"

297
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:44,630
then to me, you're the "wind."

298
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:46,720
Always running free,

299
00:22:48,150 --> 00:22:49,530
and taking me along with you.

300
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,570
Wait.

301
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:25,260
Sorry.

302
00:23:25,950 --> 00:23:27,250
I couldn't help myself.

303
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:31,020
What if someone sees us?

304
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:34,590
Didn't you just shout your confession?

305
00:23:37,210 --> 00:23:38,210
Honestly...

306
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:45,210
We were once blurred and uncertain,

307
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:48,260
but now we have clear outlines.

308
00:23:49,420 --> 00:23:50,820
Our different colors

309
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:52,710
are slowly blending together.

310
00:23:55,250 --> 00:23:57,670
To never lose sight of what's real,

311
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:05,180
and to... stop wandering.

312
00:24:13,940 --> 00:24:14,940
Kanata.

313
00:24:20,930 --> 00:24:22,020
What are you listening to?

314
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,190
That song you recommended.

315
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:27,070
Man, this brings back memories.

316
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:30,760
Here.

317
00:24:31,300 --> 00:24:32,320
Thanks.

318
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:53,840
Hey.

319
00:24:56,410 --> 00:24:58,090
When did you first start liking me?

320
00:25:00,990 --> 00:25:02,090
Hmm...

321
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:09,830
Probably from the moment
you made me your "sun."
